title: GET
extract: to receive or come to have possession, use, or enjoyment of: to get a birthday present; to get a pension. to cause to be in one's possession or succeed in having available for one's use or enjoyment; obtain; acquire: to get a good price after bargaining; to get oil by drilling; to get information.
